  "description": "A balanced South Indian lunch bowl where legumes, vegetables, and whole grains carry the dish instead of excess fat. Chayote Coconut Stew with Red Rice brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a pot on medium heat and soften onion, ginger, chilli, and curry leaves for 3 minutes without browning.",
    "Add the vegetable and 250 ml water, cover, and cook on medium-low heat for 8 minutes until almost tender.",
    "Add the cooked pulse accent, coconut milk, and salt and simmer gently on low heat for 5 minutes until the broth lightly coats the spoon.",
    "Serve the stew over or beside the cooked grain."
  ],
